social workers iam thinking about becoming one what are the good and bad parts of your job well for starters the pay is on the low side you won't starve but you won't be eating steak every night of dinner either i get frustrated when i go way beyond the call of duty to help someone and they are not in the least bit grateful and expected more on the positive side it is very rewarding when you help someone and it really effects their life positively being a social worker makes me appreciate my children more and makes me grateful for the things i have that i take for granted it also makes me more empathic as i was very jaded as a police officer Goodness and value theory Phoebe Halliwell Constitution of the Turkish Republic of Northern Cyprus Economic inequality Poker jargon Freeters Efficiency wages Graduate school 1957 World Series Altruism Audrey Hepburn Theory of conduct Unemployment Principal-agent problem Social Security (United States) Eight hour day Ethics Socialist Workers Party (United States) Anorexia nervosa Mojave people American Civil Rights Movement (1955-1968) Taxation in the United States Pakistani cricket team in West Indies in 2005 Jade Empire Shit Professor Steak Hamburger Tariff Passover Trade union Kibbutz The Apprentice 2 Sweatshop Labor theory of value Past and present anarchist communities Barbecue 2000 Australian Grand Prix Bureaucracy Social rule Procrastination Division of labour Social psychology Gratitude Social Credit Martial Stuttering Criticism of government response to Hurricane Katrina Progressive tax Microeconomics Merit Simone Weil Humphrey Bogart Human nature Chess terminology Charles Dickens Karma David Dubinsky Boom Town (Doctor Who) Guess Who's Coming to Criticize Dinner? Little Britain Capitalism Minimum wage Diffraction grating Civil rights Psychotherapy Snooker Pitaten Education in the People's Republic of China Katelyn Faber Social justice Elderly people in Japan Economics Outsourcing Yogiisms Sumo Tax Anarchism and society T